2023-10-12T13:58:38.064Z","cooked":"<p>The wpilib <a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/hardware-apis/misc/addressable-leds.html">documention for the Addressable LED</a> is a good starting place</p>
<p>This <a href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/addressable-led-effects/404439">topic</a> I posted on a couple of seasons ago has links  our sample code and how to use led in simulation</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":18,"updated_at":"2023-10-12T13:58:38.064Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":380,"readers_count":379,"score":161.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":442223,"topic_slug":"programming-leds-candle-vs-rio-vs-ardunio","display_username":"Brad","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/hardware-apis/misc/addressable-leds.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Addressable LEDs — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":75},{"url":"https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/addressable-led-effects/404439","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"Addressable LED Effects","clicks":23}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":38557,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"5126 Codenator / Electrical, CSA, FTAA, Inspector "},"post_url":"/t/programming-leds-candle-vs-rio-vs-ardunio/442223/2","custom_user_title":"5126 Codenator / Electrical, CSA, FTAA, Inspector ","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3239442,"name":"","username":"LPryor","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/lpryor/{size}/220287_2.png","created_at":"2023-10-12T14:14:45.098Z","cooked":"<p>Don’t forget the REV Blinkin as another option.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":18,"updated_at":"2023-10-12T14:14:45.098Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":359,"readers_count":358,"score":111.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":442223,"topic_slug":"programming-leds-candle-vs-rio-vs-ardunio","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":2}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":55309,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Mentor 8280, President Motor City Alliance"},"post_url":"/t/programming-leds-candle-vs-rio-vs-ardunio/442223/3","custom_user_title":"Mentor 8280, President Motor City Alliance","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":2}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":2,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3239529,"name":"Drakxii","username":"Drakxii","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/d/4da419/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-10-12T15:23:49.969Z","cooked":"<p>How many LEDs do you want to add and do you want them to react to anything the robot is doing?</p>
<p>While there are other types of LED lightning options given your questions, I am assuming you are going for 5V addressable LEDs.</p>
<p>With that assumption, if you are only want to light up a few LEDs the RoboRio can be a good option.  You can wire up a full string to the RoboRio but it alone won’t be able to provide enough power (Amps) so you would need a secondary power supply and a secondary power supply wired up incorrectly can be dangerous to your RoboRio so I wouldn’t recommend it with the other options available.</p>
<p>If you are looking to hook up a normal amount of light both the REV Blinkin and the CANdle are good options as they already come with the power supply needed to run a normal amount of LEDs (5A from the blinkin and 6A from the CANdle).  Personally I would go with a CANdle over a Blinkin as it has more options on what your lights would look like, but if blinkin has the light modes you want it would let you save a few bucks.</p>
<p>Finally if you want enough lights to blind people or just want a electrical/programing project an Arduino with a power supply is the way to go.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":18,"updated_at":"2023-10-12T15:24:08.488Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":5,"reads":340,"readers_count":339,"score":93.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":442223,"topic_slug":"programming-leds-candle-vs-rio-vs-ardunio","display_username":"Drakxii","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":23134,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"2582/5941 Mentor, CSA, and RI "},"post_url":"/t/programming-leds-candle-vs-rio-vs-ardunio/442223/4","custom_user_title":"2582/5941 Mentor, CSA, and RI ","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3239808,"name":"","username":"Hollisms","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/hollisms/{size}/110925_2.png","created_at":"2023-10-12T18:45:45.811Z","cooked":"<p>We’ve done them all…  We’ll use the CANdle until a new option hits the market.</p>
